		<td><b>Which assembler should I be using?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm really trying to get into this NES coding scene however, a lot of the documentation that I've been reading is pretty old and refers to outdated stuff. <br /><br />For example I'm currently reading a tutorial which says to use the P65 assembler, but when I go to the site to download it, it says a newer one called Ophis is available. So which is the best one that people use around here?<br /><br />Thanks.<br /><br />[edit] I just installed Ophis Assembler, but I dislike very much command line programs. Why can't it be a simple GUI program?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
