		<td><b>tepples</b> [ Fri Dec 19, 2014 5:35 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Which assembler should I be using?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The ones most commonly used around here are ASM6 and ca65 (the latter is <a href="http://cc65.github.io/cc65/" class="postlink">cc65</a> without the C compiler component). I've made a <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=22&amp;t=7991" class="postlink">template for NES projects using ca65</a>, which now includes detailed instructions on how to install everything.<br /><br />But if you're using 32-bit Windows, it'll be complicated to get ca65 installed because the binaries are for 64-bit Windows nowadays, despite it not benefiting from multi-gigabyte address space in any way that I'm aware of.<br /><br />If you want a GUI, use NESICIDE by Christopher Pow (cpow on this board), which wraps ca65.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
