		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />okay guys. I actually do know how to use command line programs (most of the time) but its the tedious text entering that I dont like. for example if you dont enter something in EXACTLY it doesnt work. <br /><br />if you know there are really old versions of MAME (arcade emulator) and getting that to work in the command line is a bi*ch. the syntax has to be perfect. you have to manually tell the program the file destination of the rom then you have to tell it the correct commands like mame -battletoads - playback recording or some crap like that. if you get anything wrong it doesnt work. <br /><br />ive had to take screen shots of me entering in the correct spacing and correct syntax just so i can reference these screen shots because i usually mess up the commands and cant get it to work. <br /><br />i like lunar ips. its an easy gui program that patches roms. which is better, having to manually type in a complicated file destination of where a rom is located and where the patch is located or just easily search or it and click on it? the worst part about file destinations is that if you have a rom thats like in several folders it becomes a mess to type in. example:<br /><br />destop/user/folder of games/folder of nintendo games/folder of snes games/folder of roms/folder of roms that start with letter S/super mario world.smc<br /><br />you want to manually type that in on a command line program twice just to patch something? NO THANK YOU.

		

